1.title: Mario Kart
1.plot: If the gaming industry has a Super Star, then it is none other than Mario himself; and, Nintendo milks this lovable celebrity for all he is worth. You've seen this beloved childhood icon do nearly everything except his actual job, now see him drive a go kart like no other.

2.title: God of War
2.plot: Take a trip back in time to Ancient Greece, as Kratos wages war on Ares to avenge the death of his family. He'll have to battle countless fiends, collect endless glowing orbs, and balance his way across way too many pitfalls. Oh and did we mention, there's boobs!

3.title: Grand Theft Auto V
3.plot: Take a trip into the virtual city of Los Santos, an almost perfect replica of Los Angeles. Play through the story as not one, not two, but three criminals who enjoy life on the edge. But if violence is not your cup of tea (then seriously why'd you get this game?), you can always relax with a quiet game of tennis, a sailboat adventure on the seas, or yoga classes.

4.title: Assassin Creed 4
4.plot: After the disappointing reviews for Assassin's Creed 3, prepare to redeem the franchise with the "Pirates of the Caribbean" game that Disney never made.

5.title: Elder Scrolls: Skyrim
5.plot: From the developers of everything Elder Scrolls comes a game so immersible you'll forget to eat, sleep, or make any friends at all. You'll spend countless hours trapped in a far off land; and when you finally emerge from the game, you'll only find disappointment and boredom back in the real world.

6.title: Star Fox 64
6.plot: Experience the Epic 1997 title "Star Fox 64" like never before. Relive your favorite moments of the Star Wars Franchise dressed as a team of four bad ass furry. It's time to show those monkeys who's boss. Oh and don't forget; Do a Barrel Roll!

7.title: Candy Crush Saga
7.plot: From the casual gaming tycoon King, comes the video game none of you want to admit to playing. It is the delight of stay at home housewives everywhere - the colourful strategy game, Candy Crush Saga.

8.title: Mortal Kombat
8.plot: From the developers who created one of the best fighting games of all time, comes a franchise that teaches children all they need to know about anatomy; but absolutely nothing about being mortal - Mortal Kombat.

9.title: Final Fantasy VII
9.plot: From Squaresoft, the company that doesn't understand the meaning of the word final, comes the best installment of the legendary series that you've actually played. Final Fantasy VII.

10.title: Portal
10.plot: From the developer who couldn't count to three if their lives depended on it, comes two of the best games of the last generation (that you can beat in a single afternoon): Portal and Portal 2.

11.title: Call of Duty: Morden Warfare
11.plot: From the company so concerned with the environment they keep recycling their only game, comes another installment of the franchise Call of Duty.

12.title: Minecraft
12.plot: From the developer, Notch, comes a game like no other (unless you count Lego, Lincoln Logs, Mega Bloks, K'NEX, Erector Sets, or playing outside) - Minecraft.

13.title: Pokemon Red and Blue
13.plot: From Nintendo, comes the game that spawned five generations of sequels, five television shows, one Magic The Gathering rip-off, seventeen movies, and a god? - Pokémon Red and Blue.

14.title: Mass Effect
14.plot: From the Canadian RPG masters (Bioware) comes a franchise full of action, drama, and butts - Mass Effect.

15.title: Diablo
15.plot: From Blizzard, the company that keeps remaking all of its original franchises, comes the series that will send you to hell and back - Diablo.

16.title: Team Fortress 2
16.plot: From Valve, the company that realized it's way easier to sell other people's games than create their own, comes the awesome sequel to a popular mod they eventually bought the rights to - Team Fortress 2.

17.title: Zelda: Ocarina of Time
17.plot: From Nintendo, comes a game so good it made you spend $30.00 on a real Ocarina, only to give up learning how to play it after five minutes. The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time.

18.title: Destiny
18.plot: The story telling of Halo, the scope of World of Warcraft, and the co-operative fun of Borderlands may eventually get patched in, but until then play the worlds hottest 7 out of 10 - Destiny.

19.title: Dark Souls
19.plot: In a world where new games are as easy as you want them to be, one franchise dares to return to gaming's roots - it's frustrating, rage inducing roots. From "From Software"comes Dark Souls.

20.title: Five Nights at Freddy's
20.plot: You tried to stay sane in Amnesia, you ran for your life in Slender, now prepare for the next step in video game horror, sitting on your ass doing absolutely nothing - Five Nights at Freddy's.

21.title: World of Warcraft
21.plot: From the company who never met a game they couldn postpone, comes a more effective form of teenage abstinence than acne, sex ed, and the catholic church combined, World of Warcraft.

22.title: Super Smash Bros
22.plot: From the company behind the Wii, and the other Wii, comes a series full of cute childhood nostalgia that you can pound the living sh*t out of - Super Smash Bros.

23.title: Pokemon Gold and Silver
23.plot: From the company that's throwing everything at the wall to see what sticks, comes the greatest video game sequel ever, Pokémon Gold and Silver.

24.title: The Walking Dead
24.plot: Not based on the popular TV show, but instead the way less popular comic book, comes a game about surviving the zombie apocalypse that's mostly people talking about stuff - TellTale's The Walking Dead.

25.title: The Last of Us
25.plot: From the studio that for some reason isn working on a next gen Jak and Daxter, comes a PlayStation exclusive so bleak it makes Killzone look like Kingdom Hearts - The Last of Us.

26.title: League of Legends
26.plot: From the studio, whose name would have you believe it made more than one game, comes one of the best games of all time that your parents didn have to buy for you - League of Legends.

27.title: FIFA 2015
27.plot: From the company that's tricked you into buying the same exact game every year for the last quarter century, comes a video game where two teams compete to score more goals based on a sport where two teams compete to roll around on the grass and pretend to be injured - FIFA15.

1.title: Kingdom Hearts
1.plot: You asked for it, so we're bringing it to you, Honest style!! While we all sit impatiently and wait for Kingdom Hearts 3 to (never) arrive, we break down all of the zippers, buckles, and character plots of the Kingdom Hearts franchise!

2.title: The Sims
2.plot: You've Simmed a city, a tower, an earth, and an ant. Now, EA and Maxis let you simulate the least interesting subject yet - you! The Sims.

3.title: Resident Evil
3.plot: From the company whose idea of a next gen Mega Man is putting him in Smash Bros, comes the first game in the franchise that defined survival horror, then turned into a comedy - Resident Evil.

4.title: Five Nights at Freddy's 2
4.plot: From the same developer comes pretty much the same game, in pretty much the same place, that you basically already played - Five Nights at Freddy's 2.

5.title: Hearthstone
5.plot: Because Warcraft and collectible card games weren nerdy enough on their own, Blizzard presents Hearthstone.

6.title: Evolve
6.plot: From Turtle Rock; creators of an epic, 4-player, zombies experience, and 2K Games; creators of an epic, 4-player, mutant-alien experience, comes something you've never seen before... an epic, 4-player, giant monster experience - Evolve.

7.title: Gears of War
7.plot: From Cliffie B, developer of your favorite games, game engine, comes the franchise brave enough to wonder, why can a machine gun be a chainsaw too - Gears of War.

8.title: Batman: Arkham Asylum
8.plot: You thought it would be easy to turn Batman into a cool video game. For 20 years, you were wrong. Now, revisit the 2009 sensation that made everyone say, "See!, now this is how you make a f!*$ng Batman game!" Arkham Asylum.

9.title: Clash of Clans
9.plot: From the developers of the Clash of Clans ripoff with army soldiers, and the Clash of Clans ripoff with... chickens, comes the cancerous mobile game built of grinding, OCD, and stealing your parent's credit card.

10.title: The Order 1886
10.plot: You've already been let down by Titanfall, Destiny, and Assassin'S Creed: Unity. Now, the latest console generation will try to justify its own existence with a six hour cover shooter with no replay value.

11.title: Five Nights at Freddy's 3
11.plot: From Scott Cawthon comes the final chapter in the trilogy we got six whole months off from... before he put us through the same sh*t all over again. Five Nights at Freddy's 3!

12.title: Mario Party 10
12.plot: From the company that spent more time raising you than your parents ever did, comes the same friendship-ruining action from Smash Bros. without all the fun game play to distract you from your hate!

13.title: Half-Life 3
13.plot: From our lord and savior comes a game that despite all the hype, didn just surpass our expectations, it took our expectations on a fancy dinner date and then proceeded to f**k our expectation's brains out! Half-Life 3!

14.title: Bioshock
14.plot: From the developer that brought you one of the most influential and revolutionary first-person shooter games ever, comes System Shock 2: Under Water. Bioshock!

15.title: Bloodborne
15.plot: From the only company who still makes games for grown-ups like Dark Souls, Tenchu, and... The Adventures of Cookie & Cream? Comes the game that put everyone who bought an Xbox One on suicide watch.

16.title: Pokemon Ruby and Sapphire
16.plot: From the company that brought us a Pokémon sequel that exceeded expectations, comes yet another Pokémon sequel that... doesn quite do that.

17.title: Lego Marvel Super Heroes
17.plot: Based on a toy that teaches kids patience, creativity, and construction comes the game that teaches kids instant-gratification, button mashing, and destruction!

18.title: Mortal Kombat X
18.plot: Because Street Fighter 5 is still a year away, and Smash Bros. Wii U doesn really count, fighting game fans will have to tide themselves over with Mortal Kombat X. Trailers that tell you the TRUTH about your favorite Video Games: Honest Game Trailers. These are the hilarious trailers the game developers don want you to see...

19.title: Twisted Metal
19.plot: From David Jaffe comes a series with all the kooky fun of Wacky Races combined with all the f**ked up sh*t from Saw that dares to ask, what if the Mad Max movies took place at a Limp Bizkit concert?

20.title: Counter-Strike
20.plot: Trailers making fun of games and their faults.

21.title: Grand Theft Auto Online
21.plot: Two years ago, Rockstar Games released Grand Theft Auto 5. One year later, they took it online, and it sucked. Now, one year after that, you can almost reliably play Grand Theft Auto Online.

22.title: Heroes of the Storm
22.plot: From the company behind the games the entire world loves and the national sport of Korea, comes Blizzard DOTA... I mean... Blizzard All-Stars... I mean... Heroes of the Storm!

23.title: Splatoon
23.plot: From the company whose games milk your nostalgia for cash like a $60 BuzzFeed article, comes the new IP inspired by the 90's Nickelodeon logo that's gonna be a real pain for Mario to clean up after - Splatoon.

24.title: Fallout 3
24.plot: From the studio who makes one good game two different ways comes the best Fallout game of all time... unless you count New Vegas... or the first two. Fallout 3! Trailers that tell you the TRUTH about your favorite Video Games: Honest Game Trailers. These are the hilarious trailers the game developers don want you to see...

25.title: The Witcher 3
25.plot: From the studio who sounds like they picked three random words out of a hat comes a franchise based on the books you never read, a sequel to the game you never played, and a follow up to the game you heard was really, really good!

26.title: Watch Dogs
26.plot: The freedom of just cause. The humor of Grand Theft Auto. And the fun of Saints Row... are not in this game. But, you DO have a phone! Trailers that tell you the TRUTH about your favorite Video Games: Honest Game Trailers. These are the hilarious trailers the game developers don't want you to see...
